cs.CE, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.EE, cs.SY 

This paper discusses the value of distributed energy resources (DERs) for residential consumers, which involves the intersection of computer science, electrical engineering, and systems engineering. Therefore, cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the financial value of improved forecasting capabilities, which falls under cs.EE (Electrical Engineering and Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
